node.text: Victoria gets REAL with me about her experience with binge eating, body image, and how being a college athlete can take a toll on your mental health. We talk about how she dealt with these challenges and her pathway to therapy and the help we all need from time to time. We end with some tips for performing under pressure, so you don’t want to miss that! My hope is that you all walk away with something that will help you improve your own mental health and remember you are NEVER alone!

node.title: Body Image, Mental Health & More with Victoria Garrick!

node.text: I had a little time on my hands today so I scrolled through my camera roll and threw together this video🤗 Grateful for all these times and these humans and can’t wait to make more memories! ❤️ @alixklineman @jenniferkessy & * @fiapogtenius we need some video with you! 🙈

node.text:
It was amazing to have the AVPs to come home to after Tokyo 🤗 we loved seeing and playing for everyone who cheered for us at the Olympics❤️ and thankful we were able to pull off victories in the two we played😅🙌🏼

But now that I have some time to marinate and digest everything from the last few months🧘🏼‍♀️☕️ I need to return to the afterglow of what we accomplished in Tokyo ✨☺️✨ I worked so hard, for so long, for a chance at 🥇 and to win it on the third attempt seems so surreal and I want to FEEL it. We were so quick to move on to the AVPs and everyone wants to know what’s next, but I’m returning to this experience and going to just live HERE for awhile, because it was harder to get here than I think anyone realizes and I’ve waited a long time for this🙏🏼 For the first time in my career I’m not immediately concerned with my next move (and tbh that’s hard for me me 😂) but I’m determined to simply love and reflect with joy over my and our journey to this point 👯‍♀️❤️💃🏼🥂🎉

A little clip of my story for @mizunovolleyballusa’s #HerOwnStory series ☺️ 

So glad I found beach and the path to continue my pro career in volleyball. There are lots of challenges on the road to success, it’s all about how you react to and navigate the adversity that determines your trajectory. I didn’t know if I was doing it “right” in the moment, I just always followed my heart, worked my 🍑 off and said yes to opportunity.

Also in honor of #WomensEqualityDay if you want to save/share this post and/or check out my ARxMizuno line that would be awesome 🛍🤗 plus there’s FREE shipping on all orders of $75+ 👊🏼 (LINK is in my bio! Or just Google - “april ross mizuno line 😉)

node.text:
The GRANDDADDY!! Manhattan Beach Open Champs!! 🏆💫🍾🎉

It was so fun to come home after the Olympics and compete at the MBO in front of a packed house for every. single. match. And to WIN! 🤯🙌🏼🙏🏼🎉 Thank you @alixklineman for being the energy leader in the final and for doing what you do! @angieakers & @fiapogtenius thank you for your dedication and time you put into coaching our team! ❤️❤️❤️

So excited to have our names going up on the Manhattan Beach Pier together again 🤗 Loved having the #ATeam out to support in person finally too! ❤️

Now for some much needed R&R 📖🧘🏼‍♀️😴😴😴

#GRATEFUL
